	 <h1 align="center">High Fidelity</h1> 
     
     
     
      <p>It's based on the Nick Hornby novel by the same name. The setting for the movie was changed from London to Chicago. 
	  It was released in 2000. The plot is about Rob Gordon, owner of a Record store and self-confesed obsesion with books, music, 
	  and movies, who is going through a break-up from his girlfriend, Laura. 
	  <br>
	  He owns "Championship Vynil Record Store" and has two workers: Dick and Barry. He analyzes his life though his past break-up 
	  as music loving man with a poor understanding of women.</p>
      Cast & Crew
	  <ul>
  <li>John Cusack as Rob Gordon</li>
  <li>Iben Hjejle as Laura</li>
  <li>Jack Black as Barry Judd</li>
  <li>Todd Louiso as Dick</li>
  <li>Catherine Zeta-Jones as Charlie Nicholson</li>
  <li>Lisa Bonet as Marie DeSalle</li>
  <li>Sara Gilbert as Annaugh Moss</li>
  <li>Lili Taylor as Sarah Kendrew</li>
  <li>Joan Cusack as Liz</li>
  <li>Tim Robbins as Ian "Ray" Raymond</li>
  <br>
  <li>Directed by Stephen Frears</li>
  <li>Produced by Tim Bevan and Rudd Simmons
  <li>Screenplay by D. V. DeVincentis,
       Steve Pink,
       John Cusack, and 
       Scott Rosenberg</li>
  <li>Based on	High Fidelity
       by Nick Hornby</li>
	   
	   
